    <title>field type menu</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="field type menu">
      <span class="shortdesc">What is a field type menu?</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=450;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M13/inars/field_type_menu.png" alt='field type menu screenshot'/>
    </div></div>
    <p>
     About to add markuped text field to the document type 'upcoming' by clicking the extended rich editor field
     in the field type menu.
     </p>
   </div>

      <p>A field type menu
       occurs in the <span href='document_type_editor.html'>document type editor</span> i.e.\
       when you have a <a href='documenttype.html'>document type</a>
       in <a href='edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>.
       In the field type menu a field type can be selected, which results in a new field of
       that type being added at the end of the
       <a href='documenttype.html'>document type</a> being edited.
      </p>
      <p>Note that you will see the field type menu also in
         <a href='review_mode.html'>review mode</a>, but you can not select the items
         from it then.
      </p>

   <p>
    Standard fields to include in a document type are:
   </p>

   <ul>
    <li><a href='../howto/add_date_to_documenttype.html'>date</a>.</li>
    <li><a href='../howto/add_string_to_documenttype.html'>string</a>.</li>
    <li><a href='../howto/add_boolean_to_documenttype.html'>boolean</a>.</li>
    <li><a href='../howto/add_markuped_text_to_documenttype.html'>marked-up text</a>.</li>
    <li>Long</li>
    <li>Double</li>
    <li>facetselect</li>
    <li>query</li>
    <li>resource</li>
    <li>text</li>
    <li>formatted text</li>
   </ul>


